        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31839",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yolau",
                        "name": "yolau",
                        "displayName": "Bogdan Martinescu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I looked into this for the past hour and I am now not sure if this is considered a bug or no.\n\t\nFacts: To have a Sendmail keep the ReturnPath you have to send an additional parameter to the PHP mail function, more precise \"-femail@address.com\"\nThe send() method from Zend\/Mail.php doesn't do that as it calls Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail with no parameters to be passed to the PHP function mail().\nThe workaround to this is to create a Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail object with the proper parameter before initiating the Zend_Mail object, but this in my view will need you to set the ReturnPath twice, once in the call $tr = new Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail('-femail@domain.com');  and the second time with the setReturnPath(\"email@domain.com\") method from Zend\/Mail.php\n\nA better approach would be to change line 949 from the file Zend\/Mail.php from:\n$transport = new Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail();\nto:\nif (!empty($this->_returnPath))\n                    $transport = new Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail(\"-f\" . $this->_returnPath);\n                else\n                    $transport = new Zend_Mail_Transport_Sendmail();\n\nThis could have a side effect though...If the user runs PHP in safe_mode() and he calls the method setReturnPath from Zend\/Mail.php this will ultimately result in a PHP error due to the addition parameter given to the mail() function.\n\nI am looking for your input on this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yolau",
                        "name": "yolau",
                        "displayName": "Bogdan Martinescu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-13T14:45:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-13T14:45:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34600",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Personally I think setReturnPath() is just wrong on Zend_Mail, it should be a Transport option.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-18T02:39:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-18T02:39:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36009",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Benjamin.\r\n\r\nI also think _returnPath parameter should be move into parameter of transport.\r\n\r\nAnd it might be better to split Zend_Mail into 3 parts, for example :\r\nZend_Mail_Sender\r\nZend_Mail_Server (it would include transport classes)\r\nZend_Mail_Reader (or _Receiver)\r\n\r\nI change this issue into next major.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-14T05:15:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-14T05:15:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36252",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't agree with the separation of names, however we should discuss this on the 2.0 Roadmap, can you add a note on the moving of setReturnPath() to the wiki page?\r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV2\/Mail+sending+and+building+enhancements+2.0\r\n\r\nSo we dont forget it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
